3.0 of 5 bubbles
Not too impressed
Dec 2018 ‚Ä¢ Family
Couple of my friends and our kids went to Hanoi for a short Christmas trip and booked a day tour for Halong Bay. It was on a weekend which prolly is part of the reason that ruined the fun. Just from the port itself, it was crowded with boats and cruises, which was pretty amazing in a way in how they pushed themselves in and out of the dock. The package tour was not too bad, as meals were included during our boat ride. It was a little hazy that day but I can imagine how beautiful that place once has been. We had couple of stops which included a cave, a bamboo ride, and a quick beach stop. We sat on the beach while the 2 kids are on their swimsuit playing sand castle. I could only imagine how beautiful that place used to be as it is now flooded with tourists and I could barely had a moment of silence to myself. Tourists coming in and out like buzzing bees and instead of sitting there in admiration of the place, I sat there thinking how humans abused nature for money. There are just too many tourists to really appreciate the place and it was impossible to take a picture of the scenery without people in the background. I would say Halong Bay is now overrated.
Written January 6, 2019
Heng How N
Singapore, Singapore7,464 contributions
2D 1N cruise
Nov 2018 ‚Ä¢ Friends
A UNESCO world heritage site in northern Vietnam and about 170km away from Hanoi, or 4 hours by car/coach.
A beautiful sea panorama with thousands over limestone islands and islets covering 1,500 sqkm.
The boat is Halong Legeng by Legacy Legend Cruises and has 18 cabins. It starts to cruise out of HaLong and later follow with lunch on boat with quite spread of pork, fish, vegetable and seafood. First activity is swimming and hiking 245 steps to the mid of the hill on Ti Top Island. After that followby afternoon tea with fruits. Learn Viet food cooking about 6:45 pm and follow by dinner.
Next morning the first activity is 6:20am for 15min Taichi excerise by the ship captain. 7:00am is simple breakfast with fruits salad, bread with butter, strawberry and egg, coffee or tea. 7:40am go for cave visit and has to walk up to the cave with 3 chambers. The last chamber is the biggest and the most ineresting up to your own imagination. Later back to the ship and cruise another 2 hours with lunch on board near the port. The cruise end by noon.
Written November 18, 2018
