Such a shame..
Aug 2018
This place is beautiful. The rocks, the formation, the bay. It‚Äôs stunning.

But.. it‚Äôs ruined.
Halong Bay is situated in the North of Tonkin, right near the Chinese border. That means the ‚Äúmorning haze‚Äù that our guide was talking about at 3pm was actually thick air pollution drifting down from China. You could hardly see the rock formations in the distance. I‚Äôd imagine on a clear day, this would look stunning, however, there is then the plastic and other contaminants in the water. Whether from China or Vietnam, who knows but there is a lot of it. The bay is over crowded with boats. The smell of diesel exhaust fumes fills the air. The one and only man made beach is over crowded, filthy and full of jelly fish. Take me back 100 years before humans destroyed this magic place. I was really unimpressed. Don‚Äôt bother.
