Ruining a World Heritage Area
Apr 2018 ‚Ä¢ Friends
We are on a three day two night Cruise on Ha Long Bay and are having a great time.
Then we noticed one of the boats sweeping rubbish off the bottom deck into the water. COULD NOT BELIEVE IT!!!!
This is my fourth visit to this beautiful World Heritage Area, and 20 years ago, we jumped off the boat and swam in the clear water, but wouldn‚Äôt think about it now with all the stuff in the water, bottles, plastic bags, a rubber glove, even a large piece of polystyrene.
The name of the offending boat is V‚ÄôSpirit Classic, we took a photo as we were extremely unhappy about the amount of rubbish in the water, we actually assumed it was the tourists themselves doing the littering, definitely not the boats.
PLEASE DO SOMETHING ABOUT THIS
