Written January 17, 2018
Lorraine C
Taupo District, New Zealand61 contributions
A magical 2 days tour with Dragon Gold Cruises - and Vanesa from C-vietnam...!
Nov 2017 ‚Ä¢ Couples
My husband and I were lucky enough to have won a trip to Hanoi and we were also determined to tick off our Bucket List a wish to visit Ha Long Bay!
We could not have done it without the assistance of Vanesa from C-Vietnam Tours! [Thu Ly Lu'ong] ...Vanesa - you were wonderful...! Your knowledge of both Hanoi [and we will review that at a later stage] and Ha Long Bay, and what was available both time and dollar wise was truly amazing: Your company is sooo lucky to have you honey :-).
Vanesa organised everything for us...all we had to do from our end here in New Zealand, was to provide her with dates when we could travel from our hotel in Hanoi - and what price structure we were looking at: The communication was excellent right the way through and before we go any further - it was such a pleasure to actually meet up with you prior to leaving your beautiful country!
Ha Long Bay! is quite simply - beautiful; before we even got there we had some fun and games with the tour being a little later than usual but this was because the US president - trump - had a motorcade thru Hanoi so all streets were closed: This would have played havoc with both tourists and those travelling to the airport....no matter ....once we were on our way with a busload of 18 we passed through the most intriguing and fascinating countryside. I want more time to do this on the next visit!
We arrived in Ha Long Bay - glorious weather too, and were tendered out to the Dragon Gold Cruise ship....met with drinks and then lunch and finally - on our merry way! A 'league of nations' with 22 different nationalities on board.
Highlights of this 2 day trip included a cooking session, making our own Spring Rolls, a magnificent dinner, visiting the Sung Sot Caves complete with stalactites and stalagmites.. and a looong trek UP and back down again! Again - I would very much like to revisit the caves....a word of warning? do NOT drink a couple beers before doing this trip :-) it's a very long way to the toilets!
Titop Island was the evening visit and in the sunset, sitting on the beach, one had to pinch oneself that we were really truly THERE!
Morning! and what a glorious calm and warm morning! breakfast and off to do some kayaking....LOVED it all...!
A visit to the Pearl Farm [I do love pearls!]....and finally we cruised back to port itself in Ha Long Bay before the 4 hour drive down to Hanoi......
I will include some of the photos taken but the one thing we HAVE to do is say the biggest ever, the 'HUGEST' thank you to Vanesa at C-Vietnam!
Without you and all your assistance, and your knowledge - it would not have been the same!
A thousand thank you's Vanesa and Dragon Gold Cruises for making a dream come true!
Written January 7, 2018
